This paper focuses on evaluating the effectiveness of different visualization types for data analysis tasks, which is a core topic in human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The paper also uses real-world datasets, which suggests a potential connection to information retrieval (cs.IR) and database systems (cs.DB). Additionally, the paper discusses the impact of data attribute types on visualization effectiveness, which could relate to natural language processing (cs.CL) and cybernetics (cs.CY).
